To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, follow these simple steps:

1. Place the symbol `\footnote{}` at the location in the document where you want the footnote to appear. For example, if you want to add a footnote to the authors list, place it at the end of the last author's name.

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}

\title{My Paper}
\author{Author 1 \footnote{First footnote}, Author 2 \footnote{Second footnote}, Author 3 \footnote{Third footnote}}

\begin{document}
\maketitle
\end{document}
```

2. Enclose the text you want to appear in the footnote inside the curly braces `{}`. For example, to create a footnote that says "This is a footnote," write `\footnote{This is a footnote}`.

3. Compile the document using a LaTeX compiler to see the footnotes in action. The footnotes will appear at the bottom of the page where they are referenced.

That's it! You've created a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX. Keep practicing and experimenting to learn more about this powerful typesetting system. Remember, every step you take brings you closer to mastering LaTeX and creating beautiful, professional-looking documents. Good luck and have fun!
